<div n="i" type="textpart" subtype="section"><ab><lb n="1"/>  <w lemma="ζάω">ζῶ<milestone unit="block"/>σιν</w></ab></div><div n="ii" type="textpart" subtype="section"><ab><lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="3" unit="character"/><orig n="unresolved">αυ</orig> <w><gap reason="lost" extent="6" unit="character"/><unclear reason="damage">ατα</unclear></w> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ζήνων">Ζήνωνος</name> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ζήνων">Ζήνωνος</name> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Θεμίσων"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Θε</supplied><lb n="2" break="no"/>μίσωνος</name> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ζήνων">Ζήνωνος</name> <w lemma="ὁ"><unclear reason="damage">τ</unclear>οῦ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἄδραστος">Ἀδράστου</name></persName></persName></persName></persName></persName> <w lemma="ἐν">ἐν</w> <w lemma="ὅς">ᾗ</w> <w lemma="σορός">σορῷ</w> <w lemma="κηδεύω">κηδευθήσετ<unclear reason="damage">α</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied></w>  <lb n="3"/> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ζήνων">Ζήνων</name></persName> <w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w> <w lemma="προγράφω">προγεγ<g ref="#projection"/>ραμμένος</w> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Αὐρηλία">Αὐρηλία</name> <name nymRef="#Χαρίτιον">Χαρί<g ref="#projection"/>τιον</name> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Καλλικράτης">Καλλικράτου<supplied reason="lost">ς</supplied></name></persName></persName>  </ab></div>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>[ . .  . ] of Zenon son of Zenon [ . . . of ?The]mison son of Zenon son of Adrastos, in which sarcophagus shall be buried the afore-mentioned Zenon and Aurelia Charition daughter of Kallikrates <gap extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The text was clearly continued on the sarcophagus. It is probable that the edict of Caracalla occurred within the lifetime of these persons.</p>
         </div>
